race.comment: BALLYHOOLIGAN (4) finished out of the money on debut two starts back then he got a long way back and was beaten 13 lengths when sixth over 1609m at Del Mar five-and-a-half weeks ago. Has the ability to put the recent run of form behind him. TAP AND GO (6) was in the firing line on the bend and ran a better race last start to finish a close second over 1609m at Del Mar after missing the placings at the previous appearance. Best figures measure up. Sure to run well. DJOSER (10) is a five-start maiden who finished seventh at his most recent outing over 1609m at Del Mar (Turf). Among the chances in what looks a nice race for him. TOPPERS AT SEASIDE (5) finished third last time out over 1609m at Del Mar (Dirt), making it six career minor placings. Has a sound record here with three top-three finishes from five starts. Among the fringe hopes.
